9. Bar Chart Panel

By clicking 📊 City Chart, an interactive panel slides out from the right-hand side of the application.

The chart provides the following information:
From the graph:
- The y-axis shows the names of the stations currently in the city.
- The x-axis shows the number of bicycles available in each station.
- The stations are arranged in descending order, i.e., the stations having the most bicycles are placed at the top and those having the least at the bottom.
- Only the stations having at least 1 bicycle are listed.
- On moving the pointer over the bar, the number of bicycles is displayed.

This makes a quick comparison possible.